latestIgtvVideos.caption: Can’t believe this magical day was almost 4 months ago ..

Grandpa Dick. My heart is broken 💔

He passed surrounded by his family Sunday January 23. 

He was the best grandfather. Growing up he was over every Sunday morning, at every dance recital, took us girls shopping, let us do his nails, played hide and go seek with us, and was so proud to introduce us to his coworkers when he would take us to pick up his paycheck. 

Not only was he a great grandfather, but he was a great friend. Talking us through heartbreak, and encouraging us through life’s journey. 

He also loved feeding Berkley table scraps 🐶 

And lastly, just like the voicemails he left so frequently - he always told us how much he loved us. ❤️ 

We were lucky to experience your love as our grandfather. I’ll love and miss you always 🙏🏻

2021 ❤️

I can’t wait to see what 2022 has in store for us @donnyflipz

latestPosts.caption:
**Trigger Warning **

Infertility to me:

It’s when, “WHEN we have a baby”, turns into “IF we ever have a baby”
Seeing everyone around you, getting the one thing you pray for
Avoiding social media & seeing another announcement post
Avoiding the mail & getting another baby shower invite
It’s immense guilt- feeling guilty & misunderstood with these feelings because you’re happy for the people around you, but it is hard not to internalize that and wonder when or IF it’ll ever be your turn
It’s watching your mom make baby blankets for others, worrying you’ll never be on the receiving end of one
It’s about 10 days of hope, followed by 14 days of praying, and about 6 days of being completely devastated each month for a year and a half while life continues to go on
It’s making that infertility appointment, but hoping you’ll never go to it because you’ll definitely be pregnant by then…
Its feelings of isolation & feeling like you no longer relate to anyone around you
It’s starting IVF & hoping it works out but preparing your heart for it to not because all you know is disappointment
It’s forming a community with others who have also experienced infertility
It’s fear coupled with hope
It’s getting a positive test, only to feel guilty because why you? Why not anyone else in the infertility community you’ve surrounded yourself with the past few months. Guilt it’s happening for you, but it still hasn’t happened for them. 

I never thought this journey would be ours, & on most days I am still in shock this is our story. Infertility sucks. A year and a half of unexplained negative tests, Dozens of doctors visits, labs, etc. It was a long, and very hard path to walk. This was by far the hardest thing I have ever gone through. But after: 

79 shots 
607 pills and vitamins
3 procedures 
1 surgery 
118 suppositories

We are finally here & we couldn’t feel more grateful and excited 🤍🙏🏻 I share this story, because I know how alone I felt at times, & encourage anyone currently navigating this phase in life to find a community of others who share in your experience.
